<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <OutputType>Library</OutputType>
    <TargetFramework>netstandard2.1</TargetFramework>
    <AssemblyName>Isaac.FileStorage.Lib</AssemblyName>
    <RootNamespace>Isaac.FileStorage.Lib</RootNamespace>
    <GeneratePackageOnBuild>false</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
    <PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>true</PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>
    <PackageId>Isaac.FileStorage</PackageId>
    <Authors>Isaac Candido</Authors>
    <Product>File Storage</Product>
    <Version>0.2.2</Version>
    <PackageLicenseFile>license</PackageLicenseFile>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/a6576171/JSONStorage</PackageProjectUrl>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/a6576171/JSONStorage</RepositoryUrl>
    <RepositoryType>Git</RepositoryType>
    <PackageTags>Storage</PackageTags>
    <NeutralLanguage />
    <PackageReleaseNotes>pnFirst</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <Description>Simple file storage solution

This package allows for data storage using serialization. It utilises a JSON-based serialisation to record data in .jk files (it's a json and it has a key, .jk is not a joke).

It is a generics-based solution that receives a key that will be used as file name and an &lt;T&gt; object. It utilises the input class structure, so no manual intervention is needed - it'll work with any given object.

Functionalities:
1. void Insert(string key, T obj): Allows insertion of a new record. The 'string key' parameter will be used as file name and T object is the data class.
2. T Get&lt;T&gt;(string key): Searches a file by name and, if possible, will deserialise to a given T object.
3. IEnumerable&lt;string&gt; GetAllKeys(): This method searches for all .jk files and returns all entries.</Description>
    <PackageIcon>acougueiro-com-faca.png</PackageIcon>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Newtonsoft.Json" Version="12.0.3" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="..\..\..\Downloads\acougueiro-com-faca.png">
      <Pack>True</Pack>
      <PackagePath></PackagePath>
    </None>
    <None Include="..\license">
      <Pack>True</Pack>
      <PackagePath></PackagePath>
    </None>
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
